# Angular Standards

Use modern Angular patterns.

## General Rules

- Use standalone components.
- Prefer Angular Signals for local and service state.
- Prefer Reactive Forms for forms.
- Avoid unnecessary NgModules.
- Keep components small and focused.
- Use typed interfaces for all data models.
- Avoid using `any` unless absolutely necessary.
- Use strict TypeScript.
- Keep business logic out of templates.
- Keep Supabase/database logic inside services.

## Folder Structure

Use this structure when possible:

```txt
src/app/
  core/
    services/
    guards/
    models/
  features/
    auth/
    dashboard/
    inventory/
    recipes/
    meal-plan/
    shopping-list/
  shared/
    components/
    pipes/
    utils/